  "id": "019d3867-45b2-7fc0-b427-8c63bf4d2824",
  "content": "# Structural Intelligence P1: JS/TS Class Inheritance and Function Calls -- Decision Record (2026-03-29)\n## What: Extended extract_js_ts_relations() with extends, implements, and calls extraction.\n## Key Design Decisions:\n1. Two-pass architecture: Pass 1 walks top-level children for imports and class declarations (including abstract_class_declaration for TS). Pass 2 does a full recursive AST walk from root for call expressions. This correctly catches calls in arrow functions, nested functions, and class method bodies.\n2. JS vs TS class heritage handling: JavaScript class_heritage directly contains the base class expression. TypeScript class_heritage wraps in extends_clause and implements_clause children. The found_ts_clauses boolean fallback handles both grammars correctly.\n3. Generic type stripping via extract_type_identifier: Handles identifier, type_identifier, generic_type (via name field), and member_expression with fallback that strips after '<'. This covers extends Bar<T>, implements IFoo<T>, and extends module.ClassName.\n4. Dynamic import() as \"imports\" not \"calls\": Recognized by checking if the function child text is \"import\" keyword. Emits imports relation with the module path.\n5. 23-item deny-list prevents edge explosion from console, promise, array, object, JSON, React DOM, CJS, and super() calls.\n## Review Findings Worth Remembering:\n- tree-sitter does NOT have an optional_chain_expression node kind. Optional chaining (obj?.method()) is parsed as a regular member_expression with an optional_chain field.\n- abstract_class_declaration is a separate node kind from class_declaration in tree-sitter-typescript. Must be matched explicitly.\n- find_chunk_by_line (nearest-chunk fallback) is more robust than find_owning_chunk (returns 0 on miss) for code between chunk boundaries.\n## What Blocked / Surprised:\n- Nothing blocked. RFC P1 design was precise and complete.",
  "source_version": "mcp",
